Here are the main changes and improvements made:

Used enum class instead of enum for better type safety.
Moved the PhiRotaryEmbedding struct to a class with private members and a private constructor. This encapsulates the internal state and provides better control over object creation.
Used std::optional instead of std::optional<Tensor> for consistency.
Used std::sqrt instead of manually calculating the square root.
Used std::vector::reserve to preallocate memory for vectors, improving performance.
Used std::move to efficiently move temporary objects when constructing and returning PhiRotaryEmbedding objects.
Used structured bindings to unpack tuples for improved readability.

These changes make the code more idiomatic, efficient, and easier to maintain in C++.
Please note that this code assumes the existence of a 'Tensor' class and related utilities (candle_nn::rotary_emb::rope, Config, Device, DType). Make sure to include the necessary headers and dependencies for these components.


