         }

         wallPosts.items.forEach((post) => {
             console.log(`https://vk.com/wall${res[0].id}_${post.id}`);
         });
     });
}).catch(console.error);
```

Please replace `'YOUR_TOKEN'` and `'PUT_USER_ID_HERE'` with your Token and the User ID respectively.

This script will output the last 10 posts URL on the console. You can modify it to get the URLs and IDs in another useful place.

Remember, VK token gives the app the functionality to read the wall posts and IDs. So, you need to generate a VK token. If you plan to make it a publicly available app, make sure to follow VK API User Authorization process. 

